A.C. Andorra adopted the euro (€) as its currency in 2015, and as the first microstate in the world officially speaks both or French and Spanish.

Andorra officially has a distinct religion of its own but is largely Christian, with just 10% of non-Christians population. The second largest number of religious group represented in Andorra are the Hindu religions. It should also be mentioned that the Roman Catholic Church is regarded by the Constitution as the religion of the state.
